Senator Barbara Boxer, a Democrat from California, has voiced her support for President Obama's jobs speech and his plan for immediate job creation. She praises the President for being both inspirational and specific in his address. Boxer specifically mentions her agreement with his proposals to rebuild infrastructure such as roads, bridges, and schools, as well as his plan to assist homeowners in refinancing. She also expresses her commitment to working on a bipartisan basis to pass the American Jobs Act.